            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "(There's a business opportunity for someone in there.)",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " These platforms are locked into the \"news\" model of an email delivered in a specified moment of time, just as many newsletter publishers are. But, for many niche sites, this \"part-work\" approach might be a more compelling opportunity. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As the Digiday article mentions:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúNews organizations have historically not really invested in these because they require some up front work and it‚Äôs a little bit different than the day-to-day format,‚Äù said Dan Oshinsky, founder of email strategy consultancy Inbox Collective. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not the first thing you tackle. This is the second wave of newsletters.‚Äù ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The raw appeal of newsletters is that they're a direct form of engagement ‚Äî they're not mediated through algorithms like search or social ‚Äî that readers sign-up to receive. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>(To those of you reading this <em>as</em> a newsletter ‚Äî thank you. I'm always grateful for people showing enough interest to put their email in the sign-up box. And it's worth taking a quick paragraph to say that. ü•∞)</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The inherent advantages of the format do not dictate the format. though. But people are already trying to define the \"perfect\" newsletter format. What will happen, because it always happens, is that most outlets will fall back on the two default options:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "The personal essay by a niche expert",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
